The paper discusses bibliometric characteristics of psychology journals, which involves analyzing citation distributions across papers within journals. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), software engineering (cs.SD), and computers and society (cs.CY). However, given the focus on analyzing citation distributions, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
